        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 5:53PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 553 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles east of Ammon, or 12 miles south of Clinton, moving northeast
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clinton, Roseboro, Garland, and Turkey.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
